# CoT / TAK receive + ledger merge (see cot/track_fusion/README.md)
# OUTPUT: **`cot-bridge.env`** sets **`COT_URL`** (skyscan PTZ/FOV/aircraft CoT publish path).
# INPUT / tracks-in: set **`COT_RX_URL`** or **`COT_INPUT_URL`** here to override PyTAK RX only
# (e.g. a different `tak://…enroll…` user than bridge output). If unset, RX uses **`COT_URL`**.
# Prefer a gitignored `.env` for enrollment tokens instead of committing them.
COT_RX_URL="tak://com.atakmap.app/enroll?host=takserver.snstak.com&username=adsbcot_snstac&token=TRunHEHQijdREuUxVOL4BUFpAGaFCElE6OMzD3bZ5VD6JKI29yljtpmKcDeH"

# Last-seen TTL for CoT rows not refreshed (seconds)
# COT_TRACK_TTL_SECONDS=30

# JSON list of [fnmatch_pattern, priority] — higher wins. Default in code favors a-*-A-M-H-Q.
# SKYSCAN_COT_PRIORITY_RULES=[["a-*-A-M-H-Q", 1000], ["a-f-A-C*", 50]]

# ADS-B rows get this skyscan_priority (C2 sorts higher first)
# ADS_B_PRIORITY=0

# Comma-separated CoT event types to omit from merged ledger (C2 selection). Defaults in code.
# COT_LEDGER_EXCLUDE_COT_TYPES=b-m-p-s-p-e,a-f-G-E-S-E,u-d-f
# Comma-separated UID suffixes (case-insensitive) to omit, e.g. bridge ping/FOV/POI.
# COT_LEDGER_EXCLUDE_UID_SUFFIXES=-ping,-fov,-poi

# Comma-separated fnmatch patterns on CoT type to omit (ground default). Omit this key entirely for defaults (a-*-G-*, a-*-G).
# Set to empty in env to allow ground tracks: COT_LEDGER_EXCLUDE_COT_TYPE_GLOBS=
# COT_LEDGER_EXCLUDE_COT_TYPE_GLOBS=a-*-G-*,a-*-G
